annotation.TEXT: Somehow, I managed to squeeze Yoshi in between those two urchins without getting hit.
Ah, so Cookie Mountain is next. (I wonder if it would be possible to get this far normally, without glitching the clock. Hmm... Maybe, if I rushed through every level.)
Okay, Forest of Illusion 4. I'll start off by accepting that generous 50-point donation from Lakitu.
Also, this pipe Lakitu has got to go.
Oh, and the game starts up immediately!
Of course, get rid of the stowaway first.
Hi, Yoshi! (Of course, that faux pas cost me the 50 points from the 1-up I could've gotten here.)
Wait, what about a star combo? You can normally get up to "2-up" per Wiggler during a star combo...
Hi, Yoshi! No points given just for his appearance, but I'm sure he'll be helpful somewhere along the way.
I'm sure most (if not all) of you can tell where I'm going with this!
Now, let's max out the score! (Which I'm assuming will be 9999.)
Eh, just 1 point per coin, as expected. Probably not worth the time normally, even with the 50-point 1-up for getting all ten coins.

Ow. Wow, I sucked there. Now, you'll notice that the scoring is different from the normal SMW's scoring. For instance, stomping a regular enemy, collecting a Yoshi coin, and grabbing a power up are all worth 10 points.
Toasty! Alright, now I can just speed through the level using the left+right glitch with Lakitu's cloud!
Stomp the P-switch now. There's enough time to reach the key block, and I can benefit from this coin arrow by stomping it here.
Oh, yeah. For whatever dumb reason, I never grabbed the moon way back in Donut Plains 4! Well, let's grab the one that's here then!
Wow, I can't seem to stop getting 40s now! So, where to next, video game?
Interestingly, hitting midpoint is worth 10 points, so some things that weren't worth points before now have a value.
Eh, so I missed a Yoshi coin. (I know where it is, too. It's in a bonus room that I skipped, but that room involves a slow skull raft ride.)
Coins!!! ...But, being worth only 1 point each, is this trip worth it?
Yeah, that 1-up was worth the usual 50 points, but I could've cleared the level long ago if I hadn't waited around for the cloud.
Sure, I'll take 50 points from this 1-up since I already have Yoshi!
Of course, not everything is worth a flat 10 points. Breaking turn blocks and collecting regular coins are worth just 1 point each, but there are certain things that are worth much more.
A shell combo is just like a stomping combo. 10 points for each hit, except for "1-up" hits, which are worth 20.
Yeah, there's definitely no glitchy results from stomping the Wigglers now.
Gulp!
After you clear a level, you're taken straight to the next level in the sequence, which is Donut Plains 1 in this case. Alright, that means I can start grabbing cape feathers!

Yep, the keyhole exit scores very nicely, at 250 points. (However, the normal goal could potentially be worth more, so it may be the better choice, depending on how early/late the keyhole exit is in the level, and how good you are at getting lots of bonus stars.)
Too bad I didn't see anything to stretch it to L-L-L-L-Ludicrous kill...
Oh, hey there, Lakitu's cloud! How's it going?

Well, I think I broke the game by triggering a keyhole exit at the last second, and now I have unlimited time to play around in the game! (Note: My final score should've been 3686, for whatever importance that may have had.)
Also, this 1-up and these coins are easy pickings.
Wow, really? Collecting the coin from a fried enemy is only worth 1 point? Probably should kill them in other ways then.
Double kill!
Barf!
Alright, so since I've spent a good amount of my time in the first two levels, I'm going to sort of rush through this one.
Hi, Yoshi!
My feather... No worries! I can get a replacement right here!
I'm pretty sure this keyhole exit is worth getting, as the normal goal is still a little ways away.
Well, I'm just going to race through this level, too.
Took a dumb hit right there... Well, at least there's a flower block just above.

Without a cape or Yoshi, the YI1 moon is probably only reachable with some tool-assisted trickery with the shell. However, the DP4 moon is certainly reachable by normal players, and so is this moon here in CI1, but good luck getting here fast enough without glitching the clock!
Yes, I could use the bonus room for extra Yoshi coins and a 1-up mushroom, but P-ballooning is so slow...
Somehow, my takeoff there worked, despite the mole interference.
The secret exit sounds like a good idea to me!
Hmm... The 8th hit was the "1-up", and I'm just getting the normal "1-up" stomp value of 20 points per stomp after that. I think the Wiggler glitch was fixed here.
KO the Chucks and get the checkpoint 1-up here, as they're worth decent points.
Couldn't resist this easy 50 points.
Now as for star combos, they work just like stomping and shelling combos: 10 per hit, or 20 per "1-up" hit.
Without having access to switch palaces, entering that pipe would be tricky, so I'm not going to bother with it.
Ultra kill!
No, it's worth 50!
Yay, got all the Yoshi coins!
...Or not. I guess the game's still confused.
Barf!
Mega kill!
So, let's take a look at this SMW Competition Cartridge by Arnpoly! Let's just press start on the mostly-the-same title screen here...
Sand cloud hit = 10 points.
Whoops! Bye, Yoshi!
Barf!
Oh, okay! Going down the pipe a second time sent me back to the title screen like normal. Well, let's start it up again and show you how time up is normally handled.
...Uhh... Umm! I don't think that was supposed to happen! I'm here in the next level, Vanilla Dome 4, but I was supposed to be whisked away to another location when time expired!
Speaking of stomping combos, I can probably get a nice one going in here!
I guess Chuck's worth 30 no matter how he's whacked. And, thwacking other foes with cape spins is worth 10 each.
Demo count: 1
Let's try not to lose Yoshi...
So, could it possibly max out at 99999?
Yeah, nothing special. I'm still just getting the normal "1-up" value from them. I'm assuming their scoring value was changed to be the same as regular enemies.
Forest of Illusion 2? Man, this level is slow. I'm sure your run would end here if you made it to this point without glitching the clock.
Hey, should I try doing a run of this without using the keyhole glitch and see how high I can score? Let me know!
Okay, I think that's enough of the koopa's all-you-can-eat buffet.
I will partake in this bonus room, however.
Also, don't forget about the Yoshi coins!
Yoshi fireballs however, are the same as Mario's. Just 1 point for collecting the resulting coin from a burned enemy.
Demo count: 2
Sure, why not? So, which level is next? (Please be Chocolate Island 5!)
Burning Chuck added 30...
Okay, Vanilla Dome 1, and I have half a minute left. Is that enough time to reach the keyhole exit here?
Okay, so here's how it works. You play through a selection of the original game's levels, and you have six minutes to score as many points as you can.
Multi kill!
I'm so outta here! Come on, Yoshi. Let's go.
I guess I'll just stampede like a rhino through these rhinos...
Demo count: Umm...
Fast-forward! (If you just saw a black flicker there, I don't know what caused it. But, whatever.)
Hey there, Lakitu's cloud again.
Good. I wanted to do that stomp combo right ever since I screwed it up during Chaos CompleXX.
Oh, I wonder how the bonus game cloud is scored...
Hello! I decided that before I finish up Chaos CompleXX, I'd give this new hack that recently appeared on SMW Central a try.
Barf!
Yeah, this is how it normally works. You're supposed to get sent straight here, so you can see your final score, then going down the pipe on the right just once will take you to the title screen.
Ah. Each hit was worth 10, except for the "1-up" stomp, which was worth 20. Doesn't seem like a profitable use of time, but maybe it was, with everything's value having been adjusted. Who knows?
Okay, forget that. I lost Yoshi.
So, I guess I could just loiter around and kill bullets endlessly for points, but that would be boring, so let's just play out the levels and see how far the game can potentially go.
Okay, back to the block factory.
Still no? Really? Okay, let's continue...
Using this blue shell and Yoshi, I think I'll have enough time.

Oh, by the way, you get unlimited lives. If you die, you simply just restart the level (and you restart at midpoint if you had hit midpoint in your current level, of course). And, there doesn't seem to be any penalty aside from a few seconds lost as you're dying.
Aw, man. I guess eating foes isn't very profitable at just 1 point per "Gulp!"...
Alright, I did! Now to grab that guy's shell and bring it back to the multi-coin block.
And hitting the goal is worth 100, plus an additional 5 points for each bonus star collected, so I get an extra 140 points from my 28 stars.
Okay, so maybe it'll max out at 65535?

Oh, by the way, reserve items aren't worth anything, not even changing to a cape feather, so no exploiting that trick here. (And the timer continues counting down during the transformation animation, so I should stop doing that.)
Barf!
Collecting the fifth Yoshi coin is worth 100, which is great.
Well, I'm going to speed up most of this level's footage, since I'm sure most of us (including me) just want to see the next level quickly.
Ooh, Forest of Illusion 1! This could get interesting...
Oh, yeah. Let's pick up Yoshi while we're here! Hi, Yoshi!
No, it didn't. Alright, let's keep going...
8-life (230-point) stomping combo!
Oh, but what's this? It doesn't cap at 9999? Well, let's see just how high it goes then...
Well, I hope you all enjoyed seeing me break yet another hack!
Alright, now you know I gotta try this! Let's stomp Wigglers!
I lost count already. You figure it out.
Alright, and now to create a block factory!
Ah, Butter Bridge 2. Alright, let's just mostly speed through this area.
Oh, come on! H hundred-thousand?! What kind of number is that?! Okay, screw this!
Alright, so next up is Chocolate Island 1.
Because of their value when I collect them all, I do want to go for the Yoshi coins.
Ooh, bumping off the Hammer Bro. from below, which was originally worth nothing, is now worth 10.
Sure, why not. I'll grab this checkpoint 1-up while I'm here!
Crashing a shell into another enemy was worth 20, which I guess makes sense, due to killing two foes at once. What about frying enemies?
Cape spin for 10, as opposed to eating for 1.
Uh, oh. When you have less than 10 seconds left, the clock begins flashing! Hurry up!
Collecting a MOOOONNN!!! is worth 150 points! Of course, there aren't very many available in this hack.
Alright, I made it to the secret exit, so let's see which level's next...
Oh, a multi-coin block. Hey... What if I... Yeah... I want to try that!
Alright, Donut Plains 4. I'm not sure if the disco shell has any major point-producing potential, but I can eat it to fly around and fart out sand clouds!
And I made it with a couple seconds to spare! Now, when time runs out...
It looks like I got an additional 20 points for getting a 1-up from coins, but that doesn't seem like much...

Oh! I guess we're done! Okay, this is where you're supposed to warp to when time runs out. This way you can get a glimpse of your final score, which is H01408 (or 1001408) for me. Then, you just go down the pipe on the right to return to the title screen.
40 yet again. Oh, by the way, you won't ever trigger a bonus game from collecting bonus stars, just so you know. (But you still want to hit the goal tape high anyway for big points.)
Will I get 40 yet again?
40 again. So what's the next level?
It's over 9000!
Alright, so let's fast-forward this until time runs out.
I probably could've kept going, but I only have a minute left, and I want to show off more things before time expires!

40 stars. That's nice, which makes this goal worth 300 points total! (Note: I checked this off camera, and if you nail the 50 mark, you do get 350 points from the goal and stars in total, but it seems like the "3-up" bonus for hitting 50 has been removed and you get no additional bonus points for it.)
This is to make it more like the Donkey Kong Country Competition Cartridge (if you haven't heard of that, there are YouTube videos of it).
Alright, so now we're in Donut Secret 1. Note: The level sequence doesn't ever change. You would end up here even if you took the normal exit in Donut Plains 1.
Over four minutes of fast-forwarding at 30x speed (according to ZSNES) later... Surely it'll cap at 999999, right?
Let's see what happens if I perform a stomping combo that would normally get me a 1-up...
How about the 1-up mushroom? Is that also worth 20?
Now, this is the original Yoshi's Island 1 all the way through, complete with this bonus room.
Pulled off a 1-up combo, just for the heck of it.
Well, now what? Should I just reset the game now, or go down the pipe another 255 times and see what happens? Yeah, let's try that!
Monster kill!
May as well pick up this flower while I'm here.
Ooh, but what about the secret exit?
Not bothering with the checkpoint 1-up on the clouds, as I'd have to dismount Yoshi for it. I will get this 1-up in the turn block though.
I hope I left a koopa shell alive over here...
Woo-hoo! I got that block factory up and running pretty quickly!
